#: ../../P/PEBKAC.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Abbrev., \"Problem Exists Between Keyboard And Chair\"] Used by support "
"people, particularly at call centers and help desks. Not used with the "
"public. Denotes pilot error as the cause of the crash, especially stupid "
"errors that even a :ref:`luser` could figure out. Very derogatory. Usage: "
"\"Did you ever figure out why that guy couldn't print?\" \"Yeah, he kept "
"cancelling the operation before it could finish. PEBKAC\". See also "
":ref:`idiot`\\. Compare :ref:`pilot-error`\\, :ref:`UBD`\\."
msgstr ""
"[略語、\"Problem Exists Between Keyboard And "
"Chair\"]サポート担当者、特にコールセンターやヘルプデスクで使われる。一般の人には使われない。クラッシュの原因が操作者のミスであること、特に\\ "
":ref:`luser`\\ "
"でさえ理解できるような馬鹿げたミスであることを表す。非常に侮蔑的。用例:「あいつがなぜ印刷できなかったか、結局わかったか?」「ああ、終わる前に操作を何度もキャンセルし続けていたんだ。PEBKACさ」\\"
" :ref:`idiot`\\ も参照。\\ :ref:`pilot-error`\\ 、\\ :ref:`UBD`\\ と比較せよ。"
